weka.clusterers

Class VoteK

  • java.lang.Object
    • weka.clusterers.AbstractClusterer
      • weka.clusterers.RandomizableClusterer
        • weka.clusterers.VoteK
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, weka.clusterers.Clusterer, weka.clusterers.NumberOfClustersRequestable, weka.core.CapabilitiesHandler, weka.core.CapabilitiesIgnorer, weka.core.OptionHandler, weka.core.Randomizable, weka.core.RevisionHandler

    public class VoteK
extends weka.clusterers.RandomizableClusterer
implements weka.clusterers.NumberOfClustersRequestable
    Proposes the number of clusters for multiple runs of SimpleKMeans clustering algorithm with different seeds based on the voting of Clustering Quality Metrics from each seed.

    Valid options are: 

     -N <num>
  Number of clusters.
  (default 5).
 
     -S <num>
  Random number seed.
  (default 10)
